  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "## 🎉 Description\r\n_burn and _burnfrom in StandardToken.sol do not allow whole balance from an account to be burn.\r\n\r\n- [ x] 🐛 This is a bug report.\r\n- [ ] 📈 This is a feature request.\r\n\r\n\r\n## 💻 Environment\r\n\r\nNext, we need to know what your environment looks like.\r\n\r\n- Which version of OpenZeppelin are you using?\r\nImporting directly from github using:\r\n import \"github.com/OpenZeppelin/zeppelin-solidity/contracts/token/ERC20/StandardToken.sol\";\r\n\r\n- What network are you deploying to? Ganache? Ropsten?\r\nRemixed JVM.\r\n\r\n- How are you deploying your OpenZeppelin-backed contracts? truffle? Remix? Let us know!\r\nRemix.\r\n\r\n## 📝 Details\r\n\r\nWhen I have a balance of 500 tokens in ERC20 compliant token using StandardToken.sol, _burn and _burn from do not allow to withdraw the whole balance due to the following line:\r\nrequire(balances[_account] > _amount);\r\n\r\n## 🔢 Code To Reproduce Issue [ Good To Have ]\r\n\r\n\r\n## 👍 Other Information\r\nFix for the problem...\r\n\r\nLine 181 needs to be changed to:\r\nrequire(balances[_account] >= _amount);\r\n\r\nLine 196 needs to be changed to:\r\nrequire(allowed[_account][msg.sender] >= _amount);\r\n",
